Fruit of the Loom Profit Surged
Sales climbed 37% to $418.6 million from $304.5 million.
   The results sharply exceeded analysts' expectations. In
late trading on the American Stock Exchange yesterday, Fruit
of the Loom shares rose $1.75 to $32.50.
   For all of 1991, the company reported net income of $111
million, or $1.60 a share, up 43% from $77.1 million, or
$1.25 a share, in 1990. Sales rose 14% to $1.63 billion from
$1.43 billion.